<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-676-577  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 676 577.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Nov 22 1990 n1240 p34(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Soft lights and data. (staff and output levels in unattended datacenters)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Davidson, Clive.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The idea of unattended data centers with robotic efficiency andlow personnel costs is an over-simplified concept.andP;  Automation isthe key to achieving an increase in the efficiency and quality ofdata center operations, but achieving this is now recognized to bea long and on-going process, not a quick solution.andP;  Leavingmillions of dollars worth of equipment unattended is unwise andthere are very real risks of security breaches, as well as threatsof fire, flood and air-conditioning breakdowns.andP;  Highly-trainedoperators are now seen as the key to achieving automation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AutomationElectronic Data ProcessingCost ReductionTrendsManagement of EDPMIS.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>